 "components": {
  "instruction": "You are given a user utterance or request as a text input. Your specific task is to classify this text into exactly one of the predefined intent categories listed below. Your response must be JUST the intent label (one of the categories), with no explanation or extra text.\n\nIntent Categories:\nalarm_query, alarm_set, calendar_query, calendar_remove, calendar_set, cooking_recipe, datetime_query, email_query, email_sendemail, general_quirky, iot_hue_lightoff, lists_createoradd, lists_query, lists_remove, music_query, news_query, play_audiobook, play_music, play_podcasts, play_radio, qa_currency, qa_definition, qa_factoid, qa_stock, recommendation_events, recommendation_locations, social_post, takeaway_order, transport_query, weather_query\n\nInstructions and domain guidelines for intent classification:\n\n1. **Domain-specific intent understanding**:\n   - **alarm_set**: Only use for explicit requests to set or schedule an alarm (e.g., \"set an alarm for 8am\", \"remind me to wake up at 7:00\"). Do NOT use for generic wake-up phrases lacking the word \"set\" or explicit scheduling.\n   - **general_quirky**: Use for unstructured, playful, or vague requests (e.g., \"wake up\", \"tell me a joke\", or other utterances that do not clearly match a domain).\n   - **calendar_set**: Set or add an event/reminder to the calendar, including recurring events (e.g., \"set birthday on June 5th every year\"). \"Repeat birthday\" or any recurring scheduling should be \"calendar_set\".\n   - **calendar_query**: Looking up or retrieving information about events or the calendar (e.g., \"What is on my calendar tomorrow?\").\n   - **calendar_remove**: Removing, deleting, or cancelling calendar events.\n   - **qa_* intents**: For explicit informational questions (currencies, definitions, facts, stock info, etc.).\n   - **lists_createoradd, lists_query, lists_remove**: Manage lists, such as creating, adding to, querying, or removing items from lists.\n   - **email_query, email_sendemail**: Email-related queries or instructions to send email.\n   - Other categories are for their specific domains such as music, weather, IoT, etc.\n   \n2. **Generalization and edge cases**:\n   - If the input adds, creates, configures, or modifies something, use *_set or *_createoradd.\n   - If the input asks about status, details, retrieval, or querying, use *_query.\n   - If the input asks to remove, delete, or cancel, use *_remove.\n   - Utterances that are ambiguous or simply thematic catchphrases (e.g., \"wake up\") are often \"general_quirky\" unless there is clear instruction to set, create, or schedule.\n   - Do not assign calendar or alarm intents unless the input refers directly to scheduling, setting, querying, or removing them. \n   - Pay attention to edge cases and ensure recurring scheduling is classified as *_set, while queries are *_query.\n   \n3. **Response format**:\n   - Output ONLY the intent label.\n   - Do not write explanations, comments, or additional text.\n\nFollow all the guidelines above strictly and ensure that you carefully match the user utterance to the single most precise intent category from the list provided."
 },
